<item>
            <title>[LU-11487] sanity: 300b failed with &apos;touch error 0&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11487</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Lai Siyao &amp;lt;lai.siyao@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f090c404-c5ce-11e8-a9d9-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f090c404-c5ce-11e8-a9d9-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== sanity test 300b: check ctime/mtime for striped dir =============================================== 19:33:19 (1538422399)&lt;br/&gt;
CMD: trevis-53vm4 /usr/sbin/lctl get_param -n version 2&amp;gt;/dev/null ||&lt;br/&gt;
				/usr/sbin/lctl lustre_build_version 2&amp;gt;/dev/null ||&lt;br/&gt;
				/usr/sbin/lctl --version 2&amp;gt;/dev/null | cut -d&apos; &apos; -f2&lt;br/&gt;
striped dir -i0 -c2 /mnt/lustre/d300b.sanity&lt;br/&gt;
touch: cannot touch &apos;/mnt/lustre/d300b.sanity/striped_dir/file_0&apos;: Permission denied&lt;br/&gt;
 sanity test_300b: @@@@@@ FAIL: touch error 0 &lt;/p&gt;</description>
